added.title: The Matchmaker
added.description: Gumball catches Darwin gazing wistfully at a photo of Teri on Elmore Plus and secretly enlists Carrie to help bring them together. But when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

added.title: The Box
added.description: The Wattersons receive an unmarked package in the mail. To distract themselves from the urge to open it they all take turns to imagine what it might contain. To Mom it could mean financial freedom, to Gumball it could mean superpowers; to whoever it's actually for, it means they're not getting their package.

added.title: The Console
added.description: When Gumball is given a cursed videogame console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality. But they'll have to level up if they're going to stand any chance against the mysterious final boss.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Panda's Sneeze
added.description: Panda bears have a very adorable (and violent!) sneeze, and our Panda is no exception. When a Vine video of his very cute sneeze goes viral, Panda becomes a cute sensation, which causes Nom Nom to try to fend off of this new challenger to his throne.

added.title: Joking Victim
added.description: When Lars pawns off all his work on Sadie, Steven helps out by working a shift at the Big Donut.

added.title: Steven and the Stevens
added.description: Steven needs a musical partner for an upcoming show, and uses a time travel device to recruit the perfect bandmate, HIMSELF!

added.title: Monster Buddies
added.description: Steven accidentally releases a monster from a gem bubble and attempts to tame its wild, violent instincts.

added.title: An Indirect Kiss
added.description: When Amethyst cracks her gemstone, Steven and the Crystal Gems go on a mission to heal her.

added.title: Mirror Gem
added.description: Steven befriends a magical mirror that can mysteriously communicate with him.

added.title: Elements Part 7: Hero Heart
added.description: A full-scale war has broken out between two kingdoms and it's up to Ooo's most unlikely hero to stop it!

added.title: Elements Part 8: Skyhooks II
added.description: With time running out, Finn and Lumpy Space Princess work together to unlock one of Ooo's greatest secrets.

added.title: Three Buckets
added.description: Finn and Fern's carefree visit to some old ruins turns disastrous.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: The Bubbles-Sitters Club
added.description: Bubbles tries to prove that she's responsible enough to own a dog.

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Skater Sumo
added.description: As Sumo and Clarence are playing outside, Chelsea and Rita skate by on their new skateboards. Enthralled, Sumo decides to build his own and join their skating team, while Clarence seems to have other ideas.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: The Substitute
added.description: After Ms. Baker takes an unexpected personal day, she is replaced by a substitute that has a hard time handling the unruly classroom. Soon, the school day devolves into chaos and it is up to Clarence to get Mrs. Baker back to where she belongs, the classroom.

added.title: Broken Boogie
added.description: When the Boogie Man loses his mojo, Uncle Grandpa steps in to help.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Uncle Grandpa
added.description: Uncle Grandpa is in trouble! If only he could call an Uncle Grandpa for help.

removed.title: The Prince and the Yucky Duckling
removed.description: A Hooded Stranger from Prince Ivandoe's past seeks revenge by attempting to ruin Ivandoe's perfect princely appearance. Bert repeatedly foils his attempts, so the Hooded Stranger kidnaps Bert and whisks him off to his lair. Time for Prince Ivandoe to rescue Bert and discover just what he did to anger the Hooded Stranger in the first place!

removed.title: Elements Part 4: Cloudy
removed.description: Before they can restore Ooo, Finn and Jake will have to escape exile in an endless sky.

removed.title: Elements Part 6: Happy Warrior
removed.description: One step closer to success, Finn and his friends fight through a new, more brutal, Fire Kingdom to find Flame Princess.

removed.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
removed.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

removed.title: Musclecup
removed.description: Feeling inadequate as a superhero, Buttercup bulks up…to the max.

removed.description: The family has waited in line outside the movie theater all night. But, hardcore fans that they are, the Wattersons are determined to be the first to see the movie and so set about battling their way to the front of the queue.

removed.title: Brother Up
removed.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

removed.title: The Sorcerer
removed.description: Gumball refuses to accept he is the only kid at school that doesn't have special powers. He convinces Mrs. Jotunheim, Hector's mom, to take him on as his apprentice but she soon learns leaving Gumball unsupervised around magic is a big mistake.

removed.title: Elements Part 5: Slime Central
removed.description: Finn and Jake infiltrate the new Slime Kingdom and are drawn into a heated skate battle.

removed.title: Steven the Sword Fighter
removed.description: Pearl tries to teach Steven the art of sword-fighting using a holographic version of himself.

removed.title: Diggin' A Hole
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa digs a hole.

removed.title: Coach Steven
removed.description: After seeing Gamet and Amethyst fuse together into the powerful Sugilit - Steven becomes determined to get super strong.

removed.title: Lion 2: The Movie
removed.description: Steven and Connie try to ride the Lion to the movie theater but Lion has other ideas.

removed.title: Clarence Wendle and the Eye of Coogan

removed.title: Sneaky Peeky
removed.description: After missing out on a chance to see the premiere of the new Robofrog movie trailer, the trio devises a plan to sneak into the theater and catch a glimpse before anyone else. However, when they accidentally damage the reel, they're forced to fix it or fess up!

removed.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
removed.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

removed.title: Pizza Steve's Past
removed.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

removed.title: Rose's Room
removed.description: Steven's desire for some alone time unlocks a new room in the Temple that answers his every wish.

removed.title: Stump Brothers

removed.description: Babs is drawn into the world of modeling by animal calendar photographer, Elmyra Duff, while Plucky grapples with a bad caricature.
